<div><h3>TA 217 - Teaching Creativity: The Main South Workshop </h3>  <hr>A class where a small group of students will learn the basic skills of teaching theatre. Clark students will run a weekly session with 12-15 students from a Worcester high school creating a theatre workshop. The students will learn how to teach improvisation, acting, and playwriting. Clark students will be mentored in curriculum and instruction techniques. By Permission Only<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=94239" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=94239&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=94239&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt1930" target="_blank">TA 112</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>Â <br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> fall & spring<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt1930"></div></div>		</td>
